list.item:
You may then wish to go round the table and get comments from:
—Gaud on the development picture and prospects in Indonesia;
—Freeman on the domestic rice prospects and PL 480 set aside.

(FYI: The World Bank and the Asian
                        Development Bank, as well as a number of private enterprises, will be
                        examining Indonesian development possibilities in the months ahead.) You may
                        wish to conclude by asking that a development program for 1968 and beyond be
                        prepared and submitted to you by, say, October 31, including: 

—major Indonesian efforts;

—contributions by other governments and international
                                institutions;

—contributions by foreign private enterprise;

—the U.S. contribution.
